Specific surface area, pore volume, and average pore diameter are determined based on the N2 adsorption-desorption isotherms. The N2 adsorption/desorption isotherms of BiVO4 and CN samples are classified as type IV according to IUPAC, whereas the MOF-808 sample exhibits type I isotherms typical of microporous materials (Fig. 4
                     ) [47]. Table 1
                      presents surface area values of 5.66 m2/g for BiVO4, 1270 m2/g for MOF-808, and 78.25 m2/g for CN, along with corresponding pore volumes of 0.036, 0.908, and 0.413 cm3/g, respectively.
